column1: What happens once in a minute, twice in a moment but never in one thousand years?
The English alphabet goes from A to Z but my name goes from Z to A. What am I?
What has thirteen hearts, but no other organs?
Most people think of me as money. But when they find me in the water, they won't get any money out of me. What am I?
You're running a race and at the very end, you pass the person in 2nd place. What place did you finish the race in?
I am so simple that I can only point, yet I guide people all over the world.
A bus driver was heading down a busy street in the city. He went past three stop signs without stopping. But the bus driver didn't break any traffic laws. How?
What kind of room has no walls or corners?
What has one eye but can't see?
What goes away as soon as you talk about it?
Everyone has me but no one can lose me. What am I?
What has hands and a face, but can't hold anything or smile?
What's the capital of France?
column2: The letter "F."  It's the only capital letter in France.

column1: An elephant in Africa is called Lala. An elephant in Asia is called Lulu. What do you call an elephant in Antarctica?
There's only one word in the dictionary that's spelled wrong. What is it?
I am the beginning of everything, the end of everywhere.I'm the beginning of eternity, the end of time & space. What am I?
I go up and down, but never move. What am I?
Often buried with fabulous wealth I'm often called wrapped up in myself. What am I?
What has keys but can't open locks?
What has a mouth but can't speak?
I sleep during the day and fly at night, but I have no feathers to aid my flight. What am I?
I fall but I never get hurt.
I'm light as a feather, but even the world's strongest man couldn't hold me for much longer than a minute. What am I?
It belongs to you, but your friends use it more. What is it?
What jumps when it walks and sits when it stands?
What can you put between 7 and 8, to make the result greater than 7, but less than 8?
column2: A decimal point. Your result would be 7.8, which is between 7 and 8.

column1: I'm very tall when I'm young but get shorter as I get older. What am I?
What can you hold in your left hand but not in your right hand?
Even if they are starving, natives living in the Arctic will never eat a penguin's egg. Why not?
column2: There are no penguins in the Arctic; they are native to Antarctica.

column1: Where do you find roads without vehicles, forests without trees, and cities without houses?
How many bricks does it take to complete a building made of brick?
What has four legs, a head, and leaves?
Poke your fingers in my eyes and I will open wide my jaws. Linen cloth, quills, or paper, I am greedy and devour them all. Who am I?
I have many eyes but cannot see.I have no mouth or nose, but always smell.Do not eat my tree or you will be,a very rare FATALITY!
What sits in a corner while traveling all around the world?
Why was 6 afraid of 7?
I am taken from a mine, and shut up in a wooden case, from which I am never released, and yet I am used by almost everybody. What am I?
What runs but cannot walk?
If you were standing directly on Antarctica's South Pole facing north, which direction would you travel if you took one step backward?
column2: North -- all directions from the South Pole are north.

column1: Why is it so easy to weigh fish?
column2: Because they have their own scales.

column1: What question can a person ask all day long, getting a different answer each time, and yet all the answers were correct.
column2: The question would be: What time is it?

column1: What are two things you cannot eat for supper?
What kind of room has no windows or doors?
He who has it doesn't tell about it. He who takes it doesn't know about it. He who knows what it is doesn't want it. What is it?
I have a little house in which I live all alone. My house has no doors or windows, and if I want to go out I must break through the wall. What am I?
What can pass before the sun without making a shadow?
What doesn't get any wetter, no matter how much rain falls on it?
I have a face, two arms, and two hands, yet I can not move. I count to twelve, yet I can not speak. I can still tell you something everyday.
What has four fingers and one thumb, but is not alive?
If you were to take two apples from three apples, how many would you have?
column2: Two. You'd have the two that you took.

column1: Who can shave 25 times a day and still have a beard?
What weighs more—a ton of feathers or a ton of gold?
column2: They weigh exactly the same, one ton each.

column1: What did one math book say to the other math book?
column2: I have a lot of problems!

column1: You are in a room with 3 monkeys. One has a banana, one has a stick, one has nothing. Which primate in the room is the smartest?
column2: You are the smartest! Humans are primates too.

column1: Name three keys that unlock no doors.
What fastens two people yet touches only one?
What happens when you throw a white rock into the Red Sea?
Mary's father has 4 children; three are named Nana, Nene, and Nini. So what is is the 4th child's name?
What do you serve that you cannot eat?
What grows when it eats, but dies when it drinks?
What can be swallowed, but can also swallow you?
The one who made it, didn't want it. The one who bought it, didn't need it. The one who used it, never saw it. What is it?
The more of them you take, the more you leave behind. What are they?
Two mothers and two daughters go to a pet store and buy three cats. Each female gets her own cat. How is this possible?
column2: There is a grandmother, a mother, and a daughter.

column1: You are pushing your car. You stop at a hotel. At that precise moment you realize that you are bankrupt. What is actually going on?
What is half of 2+2?
column2: 3 (half of 2 is 1, and then 1 plus 2 is 3)

column1: How can you put you left hand in your right pocket and put your right hand in your left pocket without crossing your arms?
column2: First put the clothes on backwards.

column1: How many times can you subtract the number 5 from 25?
column2: Only once. After that, you will be subtracting 5 from 20, then 5 from 15, etc.

column1: If you have it, you want to share it, but if you share it, you don't have it. What is it?
What kind of cake does a mouse eat on its birthday?
What's the difference between here and there?
What is better than the best thing, and worse than the worst thing?
What can burn the eyes, sting the mouth, yet be eaten?
How many seconds are there in a year?
column2: 12 (January second, February second and so on)

column1: Which moves faster: heat or cold?
column2: Heat, everybody can catch a cold.

column1: If two's company, and three's a crowd, what are four and five?
What three numbers have the same answer when added together and multiplied together?
While walking across a bridge I saw a boat full of people. Yet on the boat there wasn't a single person. Why?
column2: Every one on the boat is married.

column1: Have you heard the saying what goes up must come down? Well what goes up and never goes down?
Why can't a man living in Winston Salem, NC, be buried west of the Mississippi?
If an electric train is going east at 60 miles an hour and there is a strong westerly wind, which way does the smoke from the train drift.
Where do fish keep their money?
What needs an answer, but doesn't ask a question?
What is put on a table and cut, but never eaten?
What kind of nut has no shell?
The more you have of it, the less you see. What is it?
What goes up and down without moving?
I know a word of letters three. Add two and fewer there will be. What is the word?
You enter a dark room. You have only one match. There is an oil lamp, a furnace, and a stove in the room. Which would you light first?
What kind of rocks are on the bottom of the Mississippi River?
What is in the middle of nowhere?
A horse is tied to a 20 foot long rope. The horse wants to get some water that is 30 feet away. The horse gets the water easily. How is this?
column2: The other end of the rope isn't tied to anything!

column1: What word in the English language is always spelled incorrectly?
What occurs once in a minute, twice in a moment, but never in an hour?
What is is that you will break every time you name it?
It lives without a body, hears without ears, speaks without a mouth, and is born in air. What is it?
From what heavy seven-letter word can you take away two letters and have eight left?
What is bigger when new and grows smaller with use?
column2: Soap (or a pencil, crayon, chalk, etc.)

column1: What is the center of gravity?
What gets whiter the dirtier it gets?
Do you know why orange juice is so smart?
Here on earth it is always true,that a day follows a day.But there is a place where yesterday always follows today! What am I?
What am I? I am the only thing that always tells the truth. I show off everything that I see. I come in all shapes and sizes. So tell me what I must be!
What turns everything around, but does not move?
Twelve pears hanging high, twelve men passing by.Each took a pear and left eleven hanging there.How can this be?
column2: "Each" was the name of one of the men passing by.

column1: What's colorless and weightless, but if you put it into a barrel, the barrel would become lighter?
What has no beginning, end or middle?
What is the moon worth?
What happens twice in a week, and once in a year, but never in a day?
Scientists have proven that cats have more hair on one side then their other side. Which side of a cat has more hair?
What has a tongue, cannot walk, but gets around a lot?
What goes around and around the wood but never goes into the wood?
If a rooster laid a brown egg and a white egg, what kind of chicks would hatch?
What did the ocean say to the sea?
A barrel of rainwater weighs twenty pounds. What must you add to make it weigh fifteen?
What won't break if you throw it off the highest building in the world, but will break if you place it in the ocean?
Take off my skin and I won't cry, but you will, what am I?
When young, I am sweet in the sun.When middle-aged, I make you gay.When old, I am valued more than ever.What am I?
What did the rib cage say to the heart?
What kind of building is the tallest in the world?
column2: A library; it has the most stories.

column1: Why did the boy throw butter out the window?
column2: He wanted to see a butterfly.

column1: What did one octopus say to the other octopus?
column2: I want to hold your hand, hand, hand, hand, hand, hand, hand, hand.

column1: What did the blanket say to the bed?
What does Frosty the Snowman eat for breakfast?
What two things aren't eaten for breakfast?
Why couldn't the Teddy Bear eat?
What's the difference between a jeweler and a jailor?
column2: One sells watches and the other watches cells.

column1: How many hamburgers can you eat on an empty stomach?
column2: Only one or part of one, because after that your stomach is no longer empty.

column1: Why can't a bike stand up for itself?
What time is it when you see an elephant sitting on your fence?
column2: Time to buy a new fence.

column1: What kind of beans can't grow in a garden?
Why do seagulls fly over the sea?
column2: Because if they flew over the bay they would be Bagels!

column1: Why did the skeleton play the piano?
column2: Because he didn't have any organs!

column1: Why is it a bad idea to write a letter on an empty stomach?
column2: Because it's much better to write on paper.

column1: What did the mayonnaise say to the bread?
How do you catch a squirrel?
column2: Climb up a tree and act like a nut.

column1: Why didn't the lobster share his toys?
What did one plate say to the other plate?
What does a bee use to brush its hair?
What kind of driver never gets a speeding ticket?
Why did the boy throw a glass of water out the window?
column2: He wanted to see a waterfall.

column1: Who was the invisible man's parents ?
What do cars, trees, and elephants all have in common?
What did one rose say to the other?
Why isn't your nose 12 inches long?
column2: Because then it would be a foot.

column1: If you threw a green shoe into the Red Sea, what would it become?
Where does a bird go when it loses it's tail?
Why are fish never good tennis players?
column2: They don't like getting close to the net.

column1: If two shirt collars had a race, which one would win?
column2: Neither one. It would end in a tie.

column1: Where can you find an ocean without water?
What runs around a farm but doesn't move?
What kind of music do mummies like?
Where do polar bears keep their money?
How do you stop a skunk from smelling?
column2: Put a clothes peg on its nose!

column1: Why does it get hot after a baseball game?
column2: Because all the fans have left!

column1: How does the ocean say hello to the sand?
What did one wall say to the other?
column2: I will meet you at the corner.

column1: What question can't be answered with a yes?
What is the one thing everybody in the world is doing at the same time?
What do you take off last before getting into bed?
